    lonnHowtoRows:[['— HOW TO USE THE CALCULATOR —','Calculate what you actually take home from your part-time job'],['1. Hourly wage','Enter your hourly wage. Norway has no minimum wage, but typical rates for young workers are 160–220 kr.'],['2. Hours per week','How many hours do you work in a typical week? Part-time alongside school is usually 10–20 hours.'],['3. Working weeks per year','Standard is 47 weeks (52 minus 5 weeks holiday). If you only work during holidays, enter the number of weeks.'],['4. Age','Under 18: no national insurance contribution. Over 18: 7.6% national insurance contribution.'],['— HOW TO READ THE RESULTS —',''],['Tax-free card (100,000 kr)','If you earn less than 100,000 kr per year, no tax is deducted. You only need a frikort (order at skatteetaten.no).'],['Gross pay','What you earn BEFORE tax. Hourly wage × hours × weeks.'],['Tax deduction','What the government deducts in tax. Calculated from bracket tax, ordinary income tax and national insurance.'],['Holiday pay','Your employer sets aside 10.2% of your salary for holiday pay. Normally paid out in June the following year.'],['Net pay','What you actually receive in your account each month — after tax is deducted.'],['— GOOD TO KNOW —',''],['Tax card','Order your tax card at skatteetaten.no. Without a tax card, 50% tax is deducted!'],['Tax return','Even if you don\'t pay tax, you must check your tax return in April.'],['Holiday pay ≠ extra pay','Holiday pay replaces your salary during holidays — you receive it when you take time off.']],
