    nhTitle:'Business or hobby?', nhDesc:'When does side income become taxable business activity?',
    nhBodyHTML:'<div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--ink2);line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:14px;">Many people have income on the side — craft sales, freelance work, rentals, crypto trading, or online content. The Norwegian Tax Administration assesses four criteria to determine whether an activity is a <b>hobby</b> (generally tax-free) or <b>business</b> (taxable).</div><div style="font-weight:700;color:var(--ink);margin-bottom:8px;font-size:14px;">The four criteria (Tax Act §§ 5-1 / 5-30)</div><div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:8px;margin-bottom:16px;"><div style="background:var(--surface2);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;padding:10px 14px;"><div style="font-weight:700;font-size:13px;color:var(--ink);">1. Duration and scope</div><div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--ink2);margin-top:4px;">The activity is intended to last over time, not just a single project.</div></div><div style="background:var(--surface2);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;padding:10px 14px;"><div style="font-weight:700;font-size:13px;color:var(--ink);">2. Capable of generating a profit</div><div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--ink2);margin-top:4px;">There must be realistic profit potential over time — it need not be profitable from day one.</div></div><div style="background:var(--surface2);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;padding:10px 14px;"><div style="font-weight:700;font-size:13px;color:var(--ink);">3. Regularity</div><div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--ink2);margin-top:4px;">Systematic and recurring activity, not sporadic one-off instances.</div></div><div style="background:var(--surface2);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;padding:10px 14px;"><div style="font-weight:700;font-size:13px;color:var(--ink);">4. At your own expense and risk</div><div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--ink2);margin-top:4px;">You cover costs yourself and bear the economic risk.</div></div></div><div style="background:color-mix(in srgb,var(--accent) 8%,var(--surface2));border:1.5px solid color-mix(in srgb,var(--accent) 20%,var(--border));border-radius:10px;padding:14px 16px;margin-bottom:16px;"><div style="font-weight:700;color:var(--ink);margin-bottom:6px;font-size:14px;">Common misconception: the NOK 50,000 threshold</div><div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--ink2);line-height:1.6;">Many believe you can earn up to NOK 50,000 tax-free. <b>This is wrong.</b> The NOK 50,000 threshold only concerns VAT registration obligation — not tax exemption. There is no income threshold for when a hobby becomes a business. The assessment is based solely on the four criteria above.</div></div><div style="font-weight:700;color:var(--ink);margin-bottom:8px;font-size:14px;">Tax consequences</div><div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(200px,1fr));gap:8px;margin-bottom:16px;"><div style="background:var(--surface2);border-radius:8px;padding:10px 14px;border:1px solid var(--border);"><div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:var(--ink3);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.4px;margin-bottom:4px;">Hobby</div><div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--ink2);line-height:1.6;">Generally <b>tax-free</b>. Exception: small jobs in private homes above NOK 6,000 are taxed. No right to deduct expenses.</div></div><div style="background:var(--surface2);border-radius:8px;padding:10px 14px;border:1px solid var(--border);"><div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:var(--ink3);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.4px;margin-bottom:4px;">Business</div><div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--ink2);line-height:1.6;">Ordinary income tax <b>22 %</b> + national insurance <b>10.8 %</b> + bracket tax. VAT liability above NOK 50,000 turnover. Full right to deduct operating costs.</div></div></div><div style="font-weight:700;color:var(--ink);margin-bottom:8px;font-size:14px;">Common examples</div><div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--ink2);line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:14px;"><b>Usually business:</b> regular freelance work, multiple Airbnb rentals with active marketing, systematic crypto trading, ongoing YouTube/streaming income, handicraft sales in an online shop.<br><b>Usually hobby:</b> one-off sales on Finn.no, occasional help for friends, creative work without profit motive, passive long-term rental of a single home.<br><b>Gray zone:</b> renting out a single property (depends on activity level), part-time creative work, crypto investing vs. active trading.</div><div style="font-weight:700;color:var(--ink);margin-bottom:8px;font-size:14px;">Key thresholds (2026)</div><div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px;margin-bottom:14px;"><div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;padding:8px 12px;background:var(--surface2);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:6px;font-size:12px;"><span style="color:var(--ink2);">VAT registration obligation</span><span style="font-weight:700;color:var(--ink);">NOK 50,000</span></div><div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;padding:8px 12px;background:var(--surface2);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:6px;font-size:12px;"><span style="color:var(--ink2);">National insurance (self-employed)</span><span style="font-weight:700;color:var(--ink);">10.8 %</span></div><div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;padding:8px 12px;background:var(--surface2);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:6px;font-size:12px;"><span style="color:var(--ink2);">Tax-free threshold for small jobs (private homes)</span><span style="font-weight:700;color:var(--ink);">NOK 6,000</span></div><div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;padding:8px 12px;background:var(--surface2);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:6px;font-size:12px;"><span style="color:var(--ink2);">Carry-back period for startup costs</span><span style="font-weight:700;color:var(--ink);">5 years</span></div></div><div style="background:color-mix(in srgb,var(--accent) 6%,transparent);border:1px solid color-mix(in srgb,var(--accent) 15%,transparent);border-radius:8px;padding:10px 14px;font-size:11px;color:var(--ink3);line-height:1.5;"><b>Tip:</b> Not sure? Contact the Norwegian Tax Administration for a binding advance ruling. Always document income and expenses from day one — regardless of whether you think it is a hobby or business.<br><i>Source: Tax Act §§ 5-1, 5-30 (lov-1999-03-26-14). Skatteetaten.no — «Hobby, small jobs and extra income».</i></div>',
    sjekkTitle:'Tax return checklist', sjekkDesc:'Forgotten something? Check common deductions you may be entitled to.',
